    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-06T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-06T06:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/824: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-06T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 6, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 6—6:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1520. My 1433, May 29. We are being swamped with enquiries regarding
                    transportation to the United States. It is imperative that we give our people
                    some sort of an answer, one way or another, without delay.</p>
                <p>We have enough people to fill another boat like the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Roosevelt</hi> If the <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> is sent here, I
                    believe we can produce between 500 and 800 passengers, more if some provision is
                    made for lower fares.</p>
                <p>Military developments, of course, could change these figures overnight but that
                    is the way it looks today. The <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> would solve
                    many of our difficulties. I hope we can have her.</p>
                <p>The loan authorization of $20,000 reached us too late to be used for the <hi
                        rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi>. May we use this fund for other vessel?</p>
                <p>Ninety per cent of those coming to the Embassy still inquire regarding the
                    possibility of travelling on belligerent vessels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
